[% META title = 'Admin Guides Template Documentation' %]
[% PageVersion = 'admin/admin_guides_template.tt,v 0.01 2025/09/15 shanta Exp shanta ' %]
[% debug %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
    [% "Debugging HostName: " _ HostName %]
    [%# INCLUDE 'debug.tt' %]
[% END %]

<h1>Admin Guides Template Documentation</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>The admin_guides template provides a dynamic section for displaying administrator-specific documentation within the documentation system. It renders admin-only content with appropriate access control indicators.</p>

<h2>Template Structure</h2>

<p><strong>File:</strong> <code>admin_guides.md</code> (Template Toolkit format)</p>
<p><strong>Type:</strong> Documentation section template</p>
<p><strong>Access Level:</strong> Administrator only</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>

<h3>1. Conditional Rendering</h3>
<p>The template only renders if admin guides are available:</p>
<pre>[% IF categories.admin_guides %]</pre>

<h3>2. Admin-Only Section</h3>
<ul>
<li>Clear admin-only designation with CSS class <code>admin-only</code></li>
<li>Visual admin badge indicator</li>
<li>Role-based access control integration</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Dynamic Content Generation</h3>
<ul>
<li>Iterates through available admin guide pages</li>
<li>Generates documentation cards for each guide</li>
<li>Displays page titles, descriptions, and metadata</li>
</ul>

<h2>Template Logic</h2>

<h3>Page Iteration</h3>
<pre>
[% FOREACH page_name IN categories.admin_guides.pages.sort %]
    [% IF structured_pages.$page_name %]
        [% page = structured_pages.$page_name %]
        &lt;!-- Render page card --&gt;
    [% END %]
[% END %]
</pre>

<h3>Card Structure</h3>
<p>Each admin guide is rendered as a documentation card with:</p>
<ul>
<li>Clickable link to the guide</li>
<li>Page title (h3 heading)</li>
<li>Description or default text</li>
<li>File type badge (if available)</li>
<li>Admin-only role badge</li>
</ul>

<h2>CSS Classes</h2>

<h3>Section Classes</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>doc-section</code> - Main documentation section</li>
<li><code>admin-only</code> - Admin-only content indicator</li>
<li><code>section-toggle</code> - Collapsible section header</li>
<li><code>section-content</code> - Section content container</li>
</ul>

<h3>Card Classes</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>doc-card</code> - Individual documentation card</li>
<li><code>file-type-badge</code> - File type indicator badge</li>
<li><code>admin-badge</code> - Admin access indicator</li>
<li><code>role-badge</code> - Role-based access badge</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Structure Requirements</h2>

<h3>Categories Structure</h3>
<pre>
categories.admin_guides = {
    pages: [
        'page_name_1',
        'page_name_2',
        ...
    ]
}
</pre>

<h3>Structured Pages</h3>
<pre>
structured_pages.page_name = {
    url: '/path/to/page',
    title: 'Page Title',
    description: 'Page description',
    file_type: 'tt' // optional
}
</pre>

<h2>Integration Points</h2>

<h3>Documentation System</h3>
<p>This template integrates with the broader documentation system:</p>
<ul>
<li>Uses structured page data from documentation controller</li>
<li>Follows documentation categorization system</li>
<li>Implements consistent styling and layout</li>
</ul>

<h3>Access Control</h3>
<p>Works with the admin access control system:</p>
<ul>
<li>Visual indicators for admin-only content</li>
<li>Role-based rendering logic</li>
<li>Integration with session-based authentication</li>
</ul>

<h2>Usage Context</h2>

<p>This template is typically included in:</p>
<ul>
<li>Main documentation index pages</li>
<li>Admin-specific documentation sections</li>
<li>Role-based documentation views</li>
</ul>

<h2>Styling Features</h2>

<h3>Visual Indicators</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Admin Badge:</strong> Clear "Admin Only" indicator</li>
<li><strong>Role Badge:</strong> Role-specific access indicators</li>
<li><strong>File Type Badge:</strong> Document type indicators</li>
</ul>

<h3>Interactive Elements</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Section Toggle:</strong> Collapsible section headers</li>
<li><strong>Card Links:</strong> Clickable documentation cards</li>
<li><strong>Hover Effects:</strong> Visual feedback on interaction</li>
</ul>

<h2>Related Templates</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>admin_access_control.md:</strong> Admin access control documentation</li>
<li><strong>adding_new_sites.md:</strong> Site addition procedures</li>
<li><strong>server_update_procedure.tt:</strong> Server update documentation</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best Practices</h2>

<h3>Content Organization</h3>
<ul>
<li>Group related admin guides together</li>
<li>Use descriptive titles and descriptions</li>
<li>Maintain consistent file type indicators</li>
</ul>

<h3>Access Control</h3>
<ul>
<li>Always include admin-only indicators</li>
<li>Use appropriate role badges</li>
<li>Ensure proper access control in controllers</li>
</ul>

<h3>Maintenance</h3>
<ul>
<li>Keep page data structure updated</li>
<li>Verify links and URLs regularly</li>
<li>Update descriptions as content changes</li>
</ul>

<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

<h3>Template Not Rendering</h3>
<ul>
<li>Check if <code>categories.admin_guides</code> is defined</li>
<li>Verify page data in <code>structured_pages</code></li>
<li>Ensure proper template inclusion</li>
</ul>

<h3>Missing Content</h3>
<ul>
<li>Verify page names in categories match structured_pages keys</li>
<li>Check for proper data population in controller</li>
<li>Ensure admin guides are properly categorized</li>
</ul>

<h3>Styling Issues</h3>
<ul>
<li>Verify CSS classes are defined</li>
<li>Check for proper admin-only styling</li>
<li>Ensure badge styles are loaded</li>
</ul>

[% END %]